cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is about stereo matching, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes two novel neural net layers for matching cost aggregation, which involves learning from data, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely. Additionally, the paper uses deep neural network models, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed layers are designed to reduce computational and memory complexity, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.GR (Graphics).
